cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "IUK: Instrumentation Universal Knowledge — A Tiered Adversarial Benchmark for AI Competency in Industrial Instrumentation and Controls"
message: "If you use this benchmark, please cite it."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Anderson
    given-names: Ryan
    affiliation: "RelayForge / Dawes Einstein Engine"
    orcid: ""
abstract: >-
  IUK is a 1,547-question adversarial evaluation for AI model competency in
  industrial instrumentation and controls. Five human-difficulty tiers
  (Technician through AI Ceiling) anchored to real human performance baselines.
  Embedded hallucination traps for known industrial standards, an independent
  binary safety gate, and verified citation integrity scoring. Results are
  reported across technical accuracy, safety performance, adversarial
  resistance, epistemic calibration, and citation integrity.
